<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: USD PLAYS KEY GAME TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM LINDGREN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tonight, USD's soccer season really begins. It could also end. 
</P>
<P>
USD plays host to No. 6 Santa Clara, NCAA co-defending champion, in a 7:30 game 
at Torero Stadium that could decide the West Coast Conference championship and 
the automatic bid to the NCAA tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The Toreros (14-1-4, 1-1) are ranked No. 16, their highest ranking ever, and 
have won eight in a row. 
</P>
<P>
The Broncos (10-2-3, 1-1-0) last year pinned a 5-0 loss on USD and have won 
four in a row. They are led by senior midfielder Jeff Baicher, who has assisted 
on 12 goals this year and scored four others. Junior goalie Chris Bauer has a 
0.80 goals-against average and five shutouts, including four in a row. 
</P>
<P>
The Toreros have six players who have reached double figures in scoring: junior 
forward Paul Gelvezon (nine goals, seven assists -- 25 points), senior 
midfielder Leo Ronces (6-7 -- 19), senior midfielder Ton Crane (6-6 -- 18), 
sophomore forward Charles Adair (5-8 -- 18), sophomore midfielder Phillip 
Button (7-2 -- 16), and freshman midfielder Toby Taitano (3-9 -- 15). JIM 
LINDGREN 
</P>
</TEXT>
