<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Intel Seeks Action in AMD Dispute: Intel said it would seek court action to 
prevent an arbitrator from awarding substantial monetary damages to Advanced 
Micro Devices in the controversy over the 386 microprocessor. The arbitrator 
ruled earlier this month that Intel had breached a licensing contract with AMD 
and said a clause in the contract barring most monetary damages was invalid. 
AMD is seeking $500 million and the rights to the 386. 
</P>
</TEXT>
