<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cooper Industries Inc.: The firm reported third-quarter net income of $92.7 
million, up 36% from the year-ago quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue was $1.5 billion, up 15%. The company attributed the higher earnings 
mainly to a stronger oil and gas market. Houston-based Cooper is a diversified 
maker of petroleum and industrial equipment, electrical and automotive 
products, tools and hardware. 
</P>
