<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Boycott, He Urged: The co-chairman of Proposition 140, Lewis K. Uhler, is 
calling for a viewer boycott of the CBS mystery "Murder, She Wrote" and its 
sponsors if a commercial with its star, Angela Lansbury, opposing Propositions 
131 and 140 remains on the air. Uhler's ire was raised after Lansbury said in 
the ad that if Propositions 131 and 140 pass, "millions of your tax dollars 
will go to politicians' campaigns" -- an apparent reference to provisions of 
Proposition 131 that would set up a system for public financing of campaigns. 
However, Proposition 140 has nothing to do with campaign financing. CLAUDIA 
PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
