<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Claudia Puig, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No Horse Jumps, Says Barker: Game-show host and animal-rights activist Bob 
Barker wants people to boycott a film in which horses jump from a 10-foot 
platform into an 11-foot-deeptank of water. "Wild Hearts Can't Be Broken," 
which is being filmed in Myrtle Beach, S.C., is about a woman who rode the 
famous Steel Pier diving horse in Atlantic City, N.J., during the 1930s. Lou 
Philips, production executive for the movie, said that producers have exceeded 
American Humane Assn. standards.Claudia Puig 
</P>
</TEXT>
