<HEADLINE>
<P>
BETTING WITH JANICE; 
</P>
<P>
THE REMATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I turned a profit for the third consecutive day as Cove Dancer came through on 
part of my $50-to-win-and-place bet in the first race by finishing second. I 
will try to keep my streak going today by betting $50 to win on Moscow Moment 
in the third race and a $50 place parlay from Moscow Moment to Rules All in the 
ninth race. 
</P>
<P>
SURELOCK lost on his $20 exacta box in the eighth race when Horsche won, but 
Via May finished fifth. SURELOCK's bet today will be $40 to win and place on 
Fille L' Argent in the eighth race. 
</P>
<P>
Janice Goldinger's Thur. bankroll: $2,317.50 
</P>
<P>
Thur. Profit: $20.00 
</P>
<P>
Current Bankroll: $2,337.50 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
SURELOCK's Thur. bankroll: $310 
</P>
<P>
Thur. Profit: $40 
</P>
<P>
Current Bankroll: $270 
</P>
<P>
Note: Janice Goldinger, a horse owner, does not bet on races her horses run in. 
SURELOCK does not own horses. 
</P>
<P>
Both players started with a $2,000 bankroll. 
</P>
</TEXT>
