<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTORCYCLIST SHOOTS WOMAN IN PARKING LOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 42-year-old Encino woman was critically wounded by a motorcyclist who 
followed her into a North Hollywood parking lot and shot her Thursday morning, 
Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Anita Green was listed in critical condition at an undisclosed hospital, 
Detective Mike Coffey said. 
</P>
<P>
The woman drove her Corvette into a parking lot behind her husband's tax 
consulting business in the 12000 block of Oxnard Street about 10:20 a.m. A 
motorcyclist who had been following her for an unknown period of time shot her 
once in the torso before she could get out the car, Coffey said. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the gunman was riding a Suzuki racer motorcycle and wearing a 
helmet, Coffey said. 
</P>
<P>
Police had not established a motive and there were no suspects. 
</P>
