<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY GROWTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thanks to reporter Leslie Berger for her article bringing attention to the 
terrible traffic in Encino. 
</P>
<P>
An inaccuracy should be clarified. The population of the Encino Hills has not 
grown since the last traffic report was done in 1978, but there has been 
tremendous growth of population in the West Valley. 
</P>
<P>
We need more cross-mountain traffic routes. It is imperative that the Reseda 
Boulevard extension be completed and that Mulholland Drive be paved between 
Reseda Boulevard and Encino Hills Drive to the east. We need to move the heavy 
flow of cars, and ensure the health and safety of the Encino Hills 
neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
LAURIE KELSON 
</P>
<P>
Encino 
</P>
