<HEADLINE>
<P>
AFFORDABLE HOUSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Traveling through east Sepulveda/Panorama City the other day, I noticed a large 
amount of construction going on. I was pleased to see some revitalization 
taking place. 
</P>
<P>
However, I was also disappointed to learn that seemingly none of it was set 
aside for lower-income housing. 
</P>
<P>
I feel there is a tremendous need for affordable housing in the San Fernando 
Valley, particularly in the northeast. The area between Sepulveda and Van Nuys 
boulevards has plenty of open space to provide some decent, inexpensive 
housing. I hope Councilmen Joel Wachs and Ernani Bernardi or city housing 
officials have looked or will look into this possibility. It would be a shame 
if this "New Sepulveda" was completed five years from now without taking into 
consideration all of its citizens. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN W. SULLIVAN 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
