<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOSQUE EDITORIAL AN EYE-OPENER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Your editorial on "The mosque no one wanted" should open the eyes and minds of 
the City Council members who misused their authority to interfere in the 
constitutional rights of religious freedom. If the design of a religious 
building is subject to the council's whims and fancies, then very soon 
Christian churches would be required not to install a cross on the building in 
order to blend with the surroundings. 
</P>
<P>
Your thought-provoking editorial and Mayor Tom Bradley's justified action to 
reconsider the City Council policy in regard to the design of religious 
buildings are landmark expressions of faith in the religious freedom granted by 
our Constitution. 
</P>
<P>
I congratulate The Times for this timely editorial, and we Muslims are very 
proud to have a newspaper in the area that stood with us in exposing the 
infringement of the constitutional freedom of religion by the City Council 
members. 
</P>
<P>
SYED M. HUSAINI 
</P>
<P>
Burbank 
</P>
</TEXT>
