<TEXT>
<P>
RTC Oversight Board OKs Major S&amp;L Sale Plan: Officials of the Resolution 
Trust Corp.'s oversight board approved a plan to sell or close about 192 failed 
savings and loan institutions over the next six months. Officials of the 
oversight board said its implementation would bring to 479 the total number of 
thrifts whose financial problems have been resolved by liquidation or other 
actions since Aug. 9, 1989. But they noted that the plan is subject to the 
congressional appropriations process and cannot be completed unless it receives 
full financing. 
</P>
