<HEADLINE>
<P>
SACRIFICING AIR QUALITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I like the Santa Monica Mountains Recreation Area. The facilities never seem 
too crowded and it's usually a pleasant afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
I probably hike in one of the park units, with my family, four or five times a 
year. 
</P>
<P>
However, my family and I breathe the air in the Conejo Valley. We face the 
gridlock on our roads. The thought of sacrificing our air quality and quiet 
lifestyle for a few more acres of parkland is frightening. What is the point of 
having parkland with Stage 1 smog alerts? 
</P>
<P>
I do not support the Bob Hope, developer-motivated, land swap. 
</P>
<P>
LORRAINE EPSTEIN 
</P>
<P>
Agoura 
</P>
</TEXT>
