BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Michael Flagg, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Management Game: If brokers are having to work harder for business in this 
slow real estate market, so are developers. 
</P>
<P>
One thing they're doing is turning more to managing other people's buildings. 
</P>
<P>
The latest wrinkle is a marriage between the Wolff Co., an Irvine developer, 
and the Seeley Co., a Los Angeles broker. The two formed a new company to 
manage commercial buildings and apartments in the West. 
</P>
<P>
Thomas U. Wall is president of the new partnership, called the Seeley/Wolff 
Property Management Co., which is headquartered in Irvine. Wall had been senior 
vice president at Wolff in charge of operations and property management. 
</P>
