<P>
NURSE STABBED TO DEATH AT HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A nurse was found stabbed to death in the utility room of her West Los Angeles 
home, police said today. 
</P>
<P>
Kathleen Powell, 34, was confronted by an attacker in her Beverlywood home, 
Police Officer Pat Lane said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim's body was found about 7:30 p.m. Thursday in the utility room of her 
house at 9730 Kirkside Road, near Hillcrest Country Club, coroner's spokesman 
Bob Dambacher said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
