<P>
TOKYO PROTEST ON MIDEAST TROOPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thousands of demonstrators marched on Parliament late today to protest the 
proposed dispatch of troops to the Persian Gulf, in the latest expression of 
anger over the government bill. 
</P>
<P>
Chanting "Protect the peace constitution," the marchers walked about 1 1/2 
miles through busy downtown boulevards before gathering in front of the Diet, 
or Parliament. They were led by members of the opposition Socialist Party. 
</P>
<P>
Organizers said 30,000 had been expected, but police put the number at about 
10,000. The demonstrators were kept near the curb by a large detail of police 
and marched peacefully. 
</P>
</TEXT>
