<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
HIGUERA HAS KNEECAP OPERATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MILWAUKEE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Milwaukee Brewers left-hander Teddy Higuera, who filed for free agency earlier 
this week, had a small bone chip removed from his right kneecap during an 
operation this morning at Sinai-Samaritan Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
The surgery was performed by Brewers team physician Paul Jacobs. 
</P>
<P>
Higuera was bothered by injuries during the 1990 season and finished 11-10 with 
a 3.76 ERA in 27 starts. 
</P>
<P>
Higuera, a 20-game winner in 1986, will be hospitalized overnight. He 
reportedly turned down a three-year, $9-million contract from the Brewers 
before filing for free agency. He made $2.125 million in 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
