THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
WORLD LEAGUE U.K. TRYOUTS SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least two days of tryouts for the World League of American Football will be 
held in London Nov. 16 and 18. 
</P>
<P>
"We are hopeful that this tryout will produce some future World League stars," 
said Jerry Vainisi, the league's vice president of football management. 
</P>
<P>
The league, backed by the NFL, opens March 23 and will play in seven countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
